Regular Expressions
/.../ -> regular expression must  write in the dotted line
^ -> it checks from the begining
$ -> it checks from the end
[a-z] -> matches only lower alphabets
[A-Z] -> matches olny uppercase alphabets
[a-zA-Z] -> matches both the uppercase and lowercase alphabets
[0-9] -> it matches only numeric value

for special character use  \
example: \@,\-,\_,\.  etc

* -> matches one or more preceeding character
. -> matches single character
?=  -> this symbol denotes that  position of any string or character deesnot need to be at any specefic position whether
        it can come in the begening or last.